code: person_expertise = dssrc |>    dplyr::select(fullName, `expertise-all`) |>    dplyr::arrange(fullName, `expertise-all`) |>    dplyr::mutate(`expertise-all`=tolower(`expertise-all`)) |>    dplyr::mutate(`expertise-all` = gsub('\\(.*\\)', '', `expertise-all`)) |>   tidyr::separate_longer_delim(`expertise-all`, ', ') |>    unique()  head(person_expertise) ## # A tibble: 6 × 2 ##   fullName             `expertise-all`       ##   <chr>                <chr>                 ## 1 A. Ian Wong, MD, PhD "jupytr notebooks"    ## 2 A. Ian Wong, MD, PhD "ml/ai tools/methods" ## 3 A. Ian Wong, MD, PhD "clinical standards " ## 4 A. Ian Wong, MD, PhD "ethical ai"          ## 5 A. Ian Wong, MD, PhD "critical care"       ## 6 Aaron Y. Lee, MD     "r"

what: Histogram of expertise count by person
title: Bridge2AI self-identified expertise analysis
code: expertise_count_by_person = person_expertise |>    dplyr::group_by(fullName) |>   dplyr::summarise(count=dplyr::n()) ggplot(expertise_count_by_person, aes(x=count)) +    geom_histogram() +   ggplot2::ggtitle("Expertise Count By Person", "All onboarded individuals") +   ggplot2::ylab('People') ## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`. people_count_by_expertise = person_expertise |>   dplyr::group_by(`expertise-all`) |>   dplyr::summarise(count=dplyr::n()) |>    dplyr::arrange(dplyr::desc(count)) ggplot(people_count_by_expertise, aes(x=count)) +   ggplot2::geom_histogram() +   ggplot2::ggtitle("Person Count per Expertise", "All onboarded individuals") +   ggplot2::ylab('Expertise') ## `stat_bin()` using `bins = 30`. Pick better value with `binwidth`.

title: Bridge2AI self-identified expertise analysis
code: DT::datatable(people_count_by_expertise)

title: Bridge2AI self-identified expertise analysis
text: now two-dimensional (heatmap) plot interactive. Draw box zoom needed. Double-click return full dataset: make large PDF version figure, use following code:
code: person_by_expertise = person_expertise |>    dplyr::mutate(value=1) |>    tidyr::pivot_wider(names_from=fullName, values_from = value)  # Now a matrix of 0/1 (integer) person_by_expertise_01 = as.matrix(person_by_expertise[,-1]) colnames(person_by_expertise_01) = colnames(person_by_expertise[,-1]) rownames(person_by_expertise_01) = person_by_expertise$`expertise-all` person_by_expertise_01[is.na(person_by_expertise_01)] = 0 library(heatmaply) heatmaply::heatmaply(person_by_expertise_01,col = c('lightblue','black'), hide_colorbar=TRUE, fontsize_row=4, fontsize_col=4, plot_method='ggplot') pdf('expertise_matrix.pdf',height=30,width=50) ComplexHeatmap::Heatmap(   person_by_expertise_01,    column_names_gp = grid::gpar(fontsize=12),    row_names_gp = grid::gpar(fontsize=12),    col=c('gray95', 'black'),    row_dend_width = unit(30, "mm"),    column_dend_height = unit(30, 'mm')) dev.off() ## agg_png  ##       2

text: NIH Common Fund’s Bridge Artificial Intelligence (Bridge2AI) program propel biomedical research forward setting stage widespread adoption artificial intelligence (AI) tackles complex biomedical challenges beyond human intuition. key step process generating new “flagship” data sets best practices machine learning analysis. Machine learning type Artificial Intelligence (AI) provides machines (like computers) ability automatically learn improve experience, without explicitly programmed. biomedical research community generates wealth data, data suitable machine learning incomplete. bringing technological biomedical experts together social scientists humanists, Bridge2AI program help bring solutions deficit : Generating new flagship biomedical behavioral data sets ethically sourced, trustworthy, well-defined, accessible Developing software standards unify data attributes across multiple data sources across data types Creating automated tools accelerate creation FAIR (Findable, Accessible, Interoperable, Reusable) ethically sourced data sets Providing resources disseminate data, ethical principles, tools, best practices Creating training materials activities workforce development bridges AI, biomedical, behavioral research communities

what: Get a ORCID work detail — orcid_work_detail
title: Get a ORCID work detail — orcid_work_detail
text: ORCID API concept work dedicated API endpoint. function calls endpoint returns single data.frame row representing work.

title: Get a ORCID work detail — orcid_work_detail
code: orcid_work_detail(orcid, put_code)

title: Get a ORCID work detail — orcid_work_detail
text: orcid character(1) orcid required put_code integer(1) put-code, ORCID API internal identifier work

title: Get a ORCID work detail — orcid_work_detail
text: Additional functionality available work record bibtex entry. Using rbibutils package, one can convert citation bibtex, latex, citations various styles, even HTML.

title: Get a ORCID work detail — orcid_work_detail
code:
